# Design system enforcement

## Tokens & geometry

- Import shape/typography helpers from `#lib/design-system` (`uiRadius`, `uiTracking`, `uiTitle`) in UI primitives; do not introduce raw `rounded-3xl`, `rounded-4xl`, `shadow-2xl`, or arbitrary `rounded-[…]` unless the file is allowlisted in `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`.
- Semantic colors stay in `app/globals.css` (`:root` / `.dark`); components use `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, etc.

## Primitive imports

- **Never** import `radix-ui`, `@radix-ui/*`, or `@base-ui/react` outside `components/ui/**`. ESLint `no-restricted-imports` enforces this. App and features must use `#components/ui/*`.

## Runtime validation

- When `variant` / `size` / theme keys come from JSON, CMS, or query params, validate with Zod schemas exported from `#lib/design-system` (e.g. `buttonVariantSchema.parse(...)`).

## CI

- `pnpm run lint` runs ESLint + `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`. Keep both green before merge.
